    "This means 30.3% of the variable names generated by DeGPT can correspond to the variable names in the source code.",
    "However, this does not mean the other variable names are meaningless since the decompiler output and source code do not have the same structures.",
    "Other variable names may be meaningful under the context of decompiler output.",
    "Considering this, we also conduct user surveys, which involve the effectiveness of variable renaming, to evaluate the performance of DeGPT from another aspect, as discussed in Section V-D.",
